The paper deals with privacy in distributed consensus algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of information-theoretic privacy also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The fact that the inputs are bounded integers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG), where bounded inputs are common. Finally, the use of consensus algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
